\begin{XTRtheorem}[$-a = (-1)\cdot a$]
We want to show that $(-1)\cdot a$ is the additive inverse of $a$. To that end
\begin{align*}
a + (-1)\cdot a &= 1 \cdot a + (-1) \cdot a \tag{$1$ multiplicative identity}\\
&= (1 + -1) \cdot a \tag{distributivity}\\
&= 0 \cdot a \\
&= 0
\end{align*}
\end{XTRtheorem}
